{
  "texts": [
    "Despite the high potential of saliency maps to support bias detection in general (see Section 5.3.1), only Grad-CAM was helpful in this task, while performance was at chance with Integrated Gradients.",
    "Similar results were found when the task was to recommend the AI for sale (Adebayo et al., 2020).",
    "Another example is the selection of chess moves (Puri et al., 2019).",
    "Participants strongly benefitted from one method of generating saliency maps, whereas two other methods even impaired performance as they either highlighted too few or too many positions.",
    "Moreover, the superiority of attribution methods can depend on other factors such as image type (Müller, Thoß, et al., 2024)."
  ]
}